Introduction

Minyoung is a South Korean singer under BBGIRLS Company and GLG. She is the leader of the girl group BB GIRLS (formerly Brave Girls) and a former member of the girl group ZZBest and the project group HavyT.

On February 2, 2016, it was announced that Brave Girls would be returning as a seven-member group after a two-year hiatus. She, alongside Yujeong, Eunji, Yuna, and Hayun, were added as new members.

Minyoung officially debuted as a member on February 16, 2016, with the group's third digital single, "Deepened." Following Yujin's departure from the group on January 13, 2017, she was appointed as Brave Girls' leader.
